text: Fantastic opportunity to build your dream home in a serene environment with beautiful trees, a seasonal stream, in a park-like setting.The location near Galbraith Mountain is highly sought after and provides easy access to nature trails and recreational activities. Close to building permit ready: The presence of a driveway, power on the property, active septic permit and completion of the wetland delineation are all positive aspects. The inclusion of 1901 sf house plans is a valuable asset, allowing you to envision the design and layout of your future home. The marking of property corners, as well as the house and septic site, ensures clear boundaries and positioning. Close to I-5, Lake Padden and all amenities.

Charming and updated historic 1910 Craftsman in the Lettered Streets! Owned by only one family for over 100 years with the original character retained. This home is located close to parks, a short bike ride or stroll downtown! Inviting features include 9 ft+ ceilings, reskimmed plaster walls and ceilings, original built-in's, millwork, refinished hardwood flooring, reglazed clawfoot tub, and window bench seating. The kitchen is complete with a breakfast nook plus retro-style refrigerator. All new period light fixtures from Rejuvenation. Unfinished, workshop-style basement, with washer and dryer (approx. 288 sq. ft). Fenced, grassy backyard. Off-street parking in driveway + street parking. Detached garage with alley access or possible ADU?

Welcome to your charming one-level home bathed in natural light! With 1740 SF of living space, this delightful home boasts 3 bedrooms, ensuring ample space. Kitchen features stainless steel appliances & overlooks the backyard. Efficient floor plan with spacious living room & wood-burning fireplace in the dining/den space off the kitchen. Hardwood floors in the kitchen & dining/den add warmth & character to the space. This home offers additional parking along with garage that provides extra space, ideal for a small workspace or storage. Step outside to the fenced backyard complete with a lovely back deck, perfect for outdoor entertaining or simply enjoying the sunshine. Great location, close to schools, parks, shopping & more.

Here is a rare discovery to build your dream home on a stunning 0.26 acre lot on the Semiahmoo Community. Having old growth fir trees, and situated in the Carnoustie neighborhood, this lot will provide its new owner with privacy as well as views of Drayton Harbor, Canadian Rockies, and White Rock, BC. Conveniently situated only 10 minutes from the US/Canadian border. Be part of an upscale Semiahmoo gated neighborhood, that offers a private golf club, tennis, fitness club, marina, restaurants, and saltwater beaches. Being only one of two lots in the Carnoustie neighborhood, don't miss out on this opportunity to call this place your forever home.

Escape to your own private sanctuary on 5 serene acres! This meticulously updated Craftsman home offers a harmonious blend of modern comfort and rustic charm. With 3 bedrooms plus a bonus room and a finished walk-out basement, there's ample space for everyone. Enjoy the tranquility of nature from your expansive deck overlooking a picturesque pond, perfect for relaxation or outdoor gatherings. Nestled in a secluded setting on a dead end road, yet conveniently located for easy access to all Bellingham has to offer. Many recent updates include a newly updated kitchen, new roof, composite deck, new exterior paint, new furnace and A/C. Don't miss this opportunity to experience the peaceful retreat you've been dreaming of!

This home is the perfect blend of comfort & charm! An inviting 3 bed, 2.5 bath home, nestled on a spacious corner lot for plenty of extra yard space & featuring a thoughtfully designed open floor plan. Functional kitchen layout w/ sleek granite countertops & stainless-steel appliances. Unwind in the warmth of the gas fireplace, creating a cozy ambiance on cool evenings. Enjoy tranquil mornings w/ a coffee on the covered front porch while you watch the sun rise. Indulge in outdoor living on your covered back deck, w/ a fully-fenced yard. Perfect for hosting summer BBQs! The large attached 2-car garage provides ample space for vehicles & storage. Just minutes from both Lake Whatcom & Barkley Village, this location couldn't be more convenient!

Quiet top floor condo situated ideally on the southside of Bellingham. Nestled away from roads and backing to a greenbelt, a private and rural feel right near Fairhaven. 2 bedrooms and a den/office ideal for working from home. Open floor plan with lots of windows & skylights filling the home w/ natural light, vaulted ceilings, and a gas fireplace. Large master w/ensuite, two closets, including a walk-in. Spacious kitchen w/ lots of storage & counter space. All appliances included. New carpet in 2022, flooring in entry, kitchen & baths. Lots of upgrades. Attached double garage with more storage, plus a private turnout for extra parking. Next to the Interurban Trail for easy access to Fairhaven, Downtown Bellingham, parks, waterfront, & more.

Spacious 3000+ sq ft home in the beautiful & peaceful Sudden Valley community. Located just over 1 mile off Lake Whatcom Boulevard this custom-built Apex home with a greenbelt backyard is close to all amenities including marina, fitness center, pool & more. Space for everyone including a luxurious primary suite on the upper level with walk-in closets, shower & its own sitting area with gas fireplace to enjoy coffee or a good book. Main level features open kitchen with newer appliances & granite counters. Light-filled living room with 2nd gas fireplace and deck facing the forest. Downstairs features generous sized bedrooms, additional living room with wet bar & guest bathrooms. 2 car garage. All situated on a low-maintenance property!

Looking for a great investment property with MIL or ADU potential? Located in Gate 3, this 2900+ sqft home features a FLAT driveway & main level living. Bright open concept with primary bedroom on the main with jack & jill closet shared by second bedroom. Utility room & half bath also on the main floor. Downstairs boasts 2 separate entries, 3 bedrooms, full bath & living area. Each floor is equipped with gas to add a fireplace. New carpet, paint, furnace & range. A little more TLC is needed, but the heavy lifting is done! Fully fenced backyard backs up to Sudden Valley owned green belt. Enjoy amenities including: golf course, community beaches, clubhouse, marina, swimming pool, trails & more! $10k closing cost credit to the Buyer.

Rare opportunity! 2132 sqft Rambler w San Juan & Canada views! Sit back & enjoy the Beach, Sound, and Island vibes. Move-in ready so you can live there as-is, collect rent as a great VRBO investment, and live the dream amid other high-value owner-occupied homes. Just relax while you soak in the Brand New Hot Tub while enjoying wonderful San Juan Sunsets from your private beach. This waterfront property is approx 3.48 acres w 97ft +/- of unobstructed waterfront. The remainder of the 3.48 acres is across the street & is a treed/undeveloped area. There is an attached studio/suite w 1 Bed-3/4 Ba and Kitchen & Laundry Rm. New Electric Gate for privacy, fully fenced on beachside with space for added parking, RV Space & 2-car garage. Great space!
nearby_schools: Ferndale School District, Lummi High School, Lummi Elementary School

text: Welcome home! This single level beauty is move in ready and has the perfect open concept layout. Enjoy the fenced back yard and spacious back deck! Conveniently located close to multiple lakes and the beginning of the Mt Baker Highway, this home is the perfect jump off for the outdoor enthusiast!

Gorgeous newer home in the heart of the Reserve at Cordata, South Springs Neighborhood. Attractive 2 level home with primary bedroom on main floor with ensuite & walk-in closet. 2 bedrooms upstairs with a Jack & Jill bathroom & laundry room. 10' ceilings, hard surfaces throughout, gas fireplace, granite kitchen, light & bright with a private back patio. Washer/dryer on both upstairs AND down for your convenience. 2 car garage. Located very close to brand new regional City Park. Close to all City services with central Community Park as well.

Amazing condo in the heart of Bellingham, located close to amenities, entertainment, local farmers market & I-5. This third story condo with elevator access features bright finishes that compliment the natural light that pours through the extra windows throughout this coveted corner unit. Open kitchen and dining space, cozy fireplace in the corner of the living room, an excellent heat source for the main part of the home. Off of the dining room is the balcony that gets nice sun during the day, overlooking the market. The primary BR features a reading nook and full bath. The extra bedroom/office boasts French doors and lots of natural light. This unit has a W/D and plenty of extra storage! Underground parking for your safety.
neighborhoods: Downtown District Bellingham, City Center Bellingham

text: Discover the allure of single-level living at this charming 3-bedroom, 2 bathroom home on Kramer Lane. Nestled at the end of the street in a peaceful culdesac, this residence boasts a fully fenced yard for privacy and outdoor enjoyment. Home features include radiant floors, skylights, vaulted ceilings, new interior paint & gas fireplace. Large 2 car garage and driveway provide plenty of off street parking. With a well-maintained interior that's flooded with natural light this home offers comfort and convenience in a serene setting. Close to amenities, schools, and parks, this property presents an ideal opportunity for those seeking a tranquil lifestyle in the heart of Bellingham.

5 bedrooms home with 3 bathrooms, 3 living rooms and 2 extra storage room. 3 car garage with 3288 finished sqft home well maintained and has a great view of the hills, daylight basement with separate entrance (if you wanted to rent out the bottom). Kitchen with wood cabinets, breakfast island, kitchen nook, fireplace in living room and back deck, lots of light. Front living room is large and great for entertaining, with formal dining space. Huge living space on the lower level great for a gaming room or 3rd living room or make it a Very Large bedroom. partial Fenced in back yard that is perfect for your garden, dogs or pool!. Large Bpnus room behind lower living room that would make a great gym or media room & smaller storage room.

Totally unique, remodeled, and cared for home in the coveted Columbia neighborhood. Remodeled with modern conveniences while preserving original character. You'll love the proximity to area parks like Elizabeth and Squalicum, and the beautiful Bham waterfront. All knob and tube replaced with Romex, roof, main sewer stack, and main bathroom all completed, with permits, in '14. Additional 1/2 bath ('22), fully finished 330 sf basement ('23), and new exterior paint ('23). Move-in ready with flexible 352 sf heated & insulated garage that can be used as shop, garage or how you see fit. Two ample-sized alley parking spaces & street parking. Fully fenced with covered porch, garden, mature blue/raspberry bushes, fruit trees, & plenty of sunshine.

Rare opportunity to own a home with a view on Marine Drive. Situated on 4 acres of land just minutes from downtown Bellingham, this property offers stunning views of Lummi Island and Canada. This charming home has 3 beds/1.75 bathrooms, 2 flex spaces, large basement with tons of potential, attached garage, hardwoods, a spacious kitchen with stainless steel appliances that convey, and all new interior paint. With plenty of space both inside and out, this property is the ideal retreat for those looking for a peaceful and picturesque setting. Don't miss out on this unique opportunity to own a piece of history in a prime location!

Spacious and comfort meets contemporary design. This home spans 3, 424 SQFT with 4 bedrooms, 3 bathrooms, and 3 versatile living spaces, creating an inviting atmosphere. Kitchen has newer stainless steel refrigerator and spacious pantry. Wet bar in upper living area with large island and bar seating. The potential for an ADU conversion upstairs or add a few extra bedrooms. This place is HUGE. Features an oversized garage with high ceilings, a maintained green space backdrop, covered patio for all-season entertaining, Mt. Baker views, and new upgrades throughoutwindows, roof, flooring, and cabinets. Plenty of parking with 2 Driveways and All just minutes from Schools and Ferndale's Main Street with quick freeway access.

Light & Bright Ferndale condo with a great floorplan! Spacious living room, open-concept kitchen with center island & all new stainless steel appliances, and a sunny dining area with access to the private balcony with a storage closet. 2 full bathrooms and 2 good-sized bedrooms, including the primary suite with a walk-in closet. In-unit laundry, new carpet & light fixtures throughout, 1 dedicated parking space, only 4 units in entire building, and low HOA dues! Located near parks, dining, shops, Nooksack River, and less than 5 minutes to I-5. Don't miss out on this Ferndale Gem!

This home exudes curb appeal and tranquility. A mid century home that blends partial modern updates with potential for the discerning buyer to customize and create their dream residence in the beautiful Edgemoor neighborhood. Expansive kitchen, open living & dining with abundant natural light, overlooks the outdoor deck, patio and the natural backdrop of a lush fenced yard. Large 3-bay, deep garage, with finished, unheated bonus area above. All set on large lot with mature landscape and a circular drive. Feel away from the hustle and bustle with all the convenience of urban living.

Let the views sweep you away. This rare South Hill lot sits high on the hill with views of the San Juan Islands, the Canadian Mountains and the Marina. Build your dream home in this desirable neighborhood within walking distance to WWU, Boulevard Park and wonderful downtown Fairhaven.

This in-city four-season gardener's paradise awaits its new owner! The 3 bed/3 bath home is 2, 911 sqft home & offers views, a south-facing deck and backyard, and exquisite plantings all around. It has been lovingly cared for and maintained, has a solar-power array on the new roof, fresh exterior paint and an electric car charging outlet in the garage. Primary bedroom on main floor with dual vanity, soaker tub and low-threshold shower. Basement has been used as MIL suite with exterior access. Downstairs bonus/game room with slider to backyard. Backyard gardening area with drip watering system fed by large rain catchment cistern. Newer kitchen appliances and flooring. High-efficiency natural gas, forced-air furnace with A/C unit.

Affordable mid century modern living in Ferndale! One of the classic three bedroom designs found in the Ferndale Terrace/Seamount area with a cool California vib. Beautiful hardwood floors grace the home with vaulted ceilings giving it a wonderful bright open feel. Oversized windows bring all day sun. Newer appliances in the kitchen. Three good sized bedrooms with the primary including a walk in closet. Second bedroom has a sliding door that leads to the back deck and yard. Private feeling patio is a nice place to relax off the kitchen. Oversized back yard with plenty of room for the pooch and gardener! Detached garage and a separate carport provides plenty of room for the cars and toys. Forced air heat and minisplit for cheap heat and AC!

Introducing this sweet single-level home with a harmonious blend of comfort and convenience.3 bedrooms/2 bathrooms, this home features recent updates of a new roof, gutters, and water heater installed in 2023, with hardiplank siding. Open living area is flooded w/natural light from large windows & skylight over the kitchen.Enjoy vaulted ceilings, fireplace, & ceiling fan for comfort year round.The primary suite is large, with a private bathroom and not one, but two closets, providing ample storage and privacy.Additional bedrooms offer versatility, with one boasting a walk-in closet, while another enjoys a prime location at the front of the home.Large corner lot location near community park, trails, picnic area and RV/Boat parking across the street!

Located on the desirable west side of Lynden, this single-level home sits on a spacious lot with many appealing features. Step inside to discover new gorgeous laminate floors and updates throughout. The kitchen features an island with quartz countertops, complimented by stainless steel appliances and a large high-end undermount sink. With three bedrooms, two bathrooms, and separate living and family rooms, this home offers both comfort and convenience. The furnace was recently replaced and house has AC. There is an abundance of storage through entire house. Outdoor enthusiasts will appreciate the privacy of the patio, large backyard, garden shed & raised garden bed. Located close to downtown, trails, shopping, & restaurants.

Welcome home to this meticulously maintained single level home in the 55+ community of Cordata Park Place. Located in a park like setting, featuring a private patio & manicured front yard. Turn-key condo with spacious 2 car garage lives like a standalone home. Recent updates throughout include stainless steel appliances, updated flooring, washer/dryer, window treatments, updated light fixtures & ceiling fans, and interior paint. Open floorplan with ample natural light, primary bedroom with ensuite 3/4 bath. Community clubhouse with full kitchen, large gathering room, & billiard room. Association offers an array of events & gatherings for residents to enjoy. Nestled within the Cordata neighborhood, conveniently located to parks and trails.

Introducing Lynden's iconic Victorian home, a true gem in the real estate market! This stunning property underwent a complete remodel in 2006 with no expense spared. Boasting 4 bedrooms, 3.25 bathrooms, and over 3, 000 SF of living space, it offers a perfect blend of modern amenities and timeless charm. The kitchen is equipped with top-of-the-line appliances, while the hardwood floors exude elegance throughout. Upstairs, you'll discover 3 bedrooms, including the primary bedroom with vaulted ceilings, a luxurious bathroom with heated floors, and the unique feature of a copper tower you can climb into. Additionally, the property includes a detached garage with an ADU above. Too many features to list. Come see for yourself!

Nestled amidst the lush greenery, youll uncover an exceptional opportunity for affordable home ownership. Whether you seek a charming starter home, or an enticing investment prospect, this little cabin in the woods awaits. Featuring an airy open floor plan on the inside, with a vaulted ceiling & heat pump to ensure year-round comfort. Outside, the well-sized lot boasts a level driveway, ample parking, spacious deck, & newly-installed gutters, with laundry and storage below. Bask in the peaceful setting while enjoying convenience of being minutes from Bellingham, Lake Whatcom, and Lookout Mountain. Flooded with natural light & backing up to Strawberry Falls Trail & Creek, you will find the promise of a serene Pacific Northwest lifestyle.

Experience vacation living in Sudden Valley residence nestled within the desirable Gate 1. This 4-bed, 2.5-bath jewel is positioned at the corner of a tranquil cul-de-sac, just a minutes away from the Marina. With a fresh coat of exterior paint, the home exudes a welcoming charm. Step inside to high-end finishes, including gorgeous hardwood floors, granite countertops, and a delightful stone fireplace. The primary bedroom is a sanctuary featuring vaulted ceilings and French doors that open to a private balcony, offering views of the lake. The deck providing the perfect venue for entertaining guests. Amenities including a golf course, swimming pool, sports courts, dog park, marina, hiking trails, and 24/7 security.

Charming craftsman home located in the Meridian School District. This property is just shy of an acre & is located on a quiet road making it feel like you are out in the country, but its only minutes to town. When entering the home, you will be met w/ huge windows & lots of natural light. The kitchen is open to the dining room & one of two living rooms. French doors lead to the 2nd living room which includes a beautiful fireplace, views of the private back yard & a door leading out to the multiple back porches. The yard is a dream w/ terraced gardens, fruit trees, tree house, gazebo & a 24X28 detached shop. Evergreen trees on the property line provide lots of privacy. Finishing the basement would add sq. feet. Great place to live!

Grab this opportunity at 2325 Valencia St, Bellingham - a prime investors delight nestled on a substantial lot. This 2-bedroom, 1-bath single-level home presents multiple lucrative opportunities: revitalize it as a charming fixer-upper, enhance its value with a detached ADU, or maximize its potential by redeveloping into a multifamily complex. Situated in a sought-after area, this property is a blank canvas ready for transformation, making it an ideal choice for those looking to build or expand their investment portfolio. Located minutes to Barkley Village providing restaurants, entertainment and many trails to explore the city just a short walking distance away!

Darling home near the end of a quiet cul-de-sac in Gate 9 where the level access and plenty of sun are the first things you'll notice! Covered side deck feels like a secret garden and the babbling creek behind the home adds to the outdoor ambience. Open concept on the main level with bedrooms upstairs. Large kitchen and dining area, half bath, laundry and living room with gas fireplace on the main floor. Upstairs, you'll find the primary bedroom with walk-in closet and en-suite bath, while a Jack-and-Jill bathroom connect the two smaller bedrooms. Very close to Lookout Mountain Trailhead. Upper roof NEW in 2024. Newer appliances, too! Area amenities include two pools, parks, playgrounds, tennis and basketball courts, beaches and more!

Like new townhome in Bellingham's Sunset Village community. This 2 story, 2 bedroom, 1.5 bath townhome is cute as a button. Featuring stainless steel appliances, quartz countertops & dark cabinetry. Walkable to shopping, dining, bus line, & trail system. Don't miss out on a great opportunity! SELLER OFFERING 2% BUY DOWN RATE!!

Welcome to your ideal one-level home in Bellaire Estates! This impeccably maintained residence features recent upgrades, including a newer roof, gutters, water heater, furnace with a heat pump, refrigerator, stove, and microwave. The entryway leads to a welcoming living room & flex space. The spacious kitchen with newer granite countertops seamlessly connects to a living area with a cozy fireplace under vaulted ceilings. The primary bedroom offers a walk-in closet, dual sinks with updated countertops & soaking tub. Outside, the level lot includes mature landscaping, a newly updated privacy fence, irrigation, & room for your small RV. Conveniently located with easy access to I-5 & amenities, this home provides tranquility in a quiet location

They say location, location, location! This house is in the perfect neighborhood for walkability to so many places and its basically across the street from Goods! There is an enclosed front porch entry and it is believed to have hardwood floors beneath the carpet in the large living room and primary bedroom. There is so much that can be done with this home, as there is a mudroom that could be transformed into an additional bath or 3rd bedroom/office space. The fully fenced (done in 2018), very private rear yard has an expansive back trex type composition deck, clothes line and there is even a 12 ft x 8 ft outbuilding and 220 power. There is so much character and potential for this sweet bungalow...you just really have to see it!

This Laurel Creek park model makes for the most relaxing home away from home. Inside, there is plenty of room to spread out between the cozy add-a-room, loft, and bedroom. Sit on the covered deck year round or in the back yard area to enjoy the beautiful greenspace around you. Use the shed for additional or larger storage items. There is no shortage of ways to have fun at this beautiful property! The Glen is zoned recreational for 120 days of use out of the year and has all the amenities you could want, including 2 pools, hot tub, tennis court, library, laundry mat, 2 clubhouses, 24 hr security, gated entry, & play areas.

Gorgeous New Construction! Located within the coveted Sudden Valley community and close to all major rd. ways. This 3 bedroom 2.5 bathroom home comes complete with Quartz Counter Tops, Stainless Steel appliances, Fireplace, Range, EZ Close Cabinets, Air Conditioning, Hardy Siding, Private Office/Den Space, Bonus Room, Extra Parking, and much more. Enjoy the peaceful country setting without having to live far from town. Act fast because this hard to find home won't last long!

High quality vacant lot located in the lakeside and golf course community of Sudden Valley. This property has level access from Bigleaf Lane, and is mostly level but does slope down at the very rear of the property - near the green-belt area. Easy building lot for a 2-story home with the garage down on the main level. The property lies adjacent to greenbelt (nature trail), which has a small seasonal drainage stream for the neighborhood. Great opportunity for a custom or spec. home for someone that wants a very natural, quiet, setting. The property has previously been surveyed - corners should still be marked.

This is your chance to own one of the original chalet-style Sudden Valley cabins! Make it your own w/ some TLC & your personal design touches. This is truly a diamond in the rough! Gorgeous vaulted ceilings w/wood planking & huge picture windows, massive wrap-around deck for year-round enjoyment & peek-a-boo views of Lake Whatcom. Main floor primary bedroom w/ full ensuite bath. Upstairs can serve as a 2nd bedroom or would make a great office/flex space & includes a 3/4 bath, walk-in closet & a cute little deck w/ lake views. The daylight basement is large & open w/double sliding glass doors that lead to the flat, lush backyard & the cozy wood stove will keep you warm in the winter! Just a block from Sofield park & 2 blocks to the marina!

Welcome to this end unit condo in the heart of Bellingham's Cordata neighborhood! With an open floor plan this unit features new carpets and plenty of storage. The peaceful back patio overlooks the community green space and has a view of the mountains during the winter months. Conveniently located just minutes from public transit, Peacehealth Medical, shopping and trails.

Charming 2 bed 1 bath bay-view Beach Cottage in Birch Bay! Discover this beautifully remodeled cottage with a view, just one block from Cottonwood Beach. Its the perfect ready-to-go Short Term Rental or year-round residence. Inside, enjoy the completely renovated space, including a new roof, windows, and on-demand tankless water heater. The modern kitchen features stainless steel appliances, quartz countertops, a tile backsplash and new cabinetry. Relax on the spacious newly installed front deck, perfect for BBQs with friends or sitting by the fire while taking in the breathtaking bay sunsets. Come and enjoy all that Birch Bay has to offer: beachcombing, crabbing, restaurants, and the recently completed Birch Bay Berm waterfront walkway!

Discover serenity in this 3-bedroom, 1.75-bath home nestled on 11.33 acres, surrounded by nature. The expansive 11.33 acres of land is subdividable, providing potential for versatile use. The well-maintained home comes complete with a 24x36 double garage/workshop in a private, secluded setting. Featuring a private shared well and septic system, the updated home boasts a new roof, contemporary vinyl plank flooring, and an updated deck. Included is a plug-in for a 30amp generator. Easy access is granted by a circular driveway, and a hidden pond adds to the property's charm. With subdivision potential minimum 5 acres per parcel, each section offers road access, power, and water connections, making this property an enchanting retreat.

High Country off grid living with skyline views of Mt Baker & the Cascades. Custom built with timbers used from the lands on 80 acres of forest crafted for ultimate privacy! Not just 1 but 2 cabins fully set up with comforts found in an urban setting. Shop space to work in, a carport for your vehicles. Main cabin features a daylight basement, large kitchen & dining, floor to ceiling custom local river rock fireplace, direct views of Mt Baker, deck for relaxing, upper loft. Second cabin is rustic & fully functional. There are cut trails to hike right from the cabin, year round creek, wildlife, a lifetime of firewood pure nature at your doorstep 365 days a year. The hard work has been done by former owner estate sale sold in as is condition

Lakeway Estates, one of Bellingham's best 55+ communities! Ideal location near shopping, groceries, bank, restaurants, Woods Coffee, public transportation and I-5 access. 1998 manu home in good condition. 1, 144 SF, 2 BR and 1.75 BA. Excellent floor plan: larger primary bedroom with 3/4 BR and large closet ensuite. Separate utility room off the hallway w/ side door external entry. Pleasant sunny, south-facing large front deck. Carport. Newer storage shed in back. Located in back of the park and next to the finely updated community center - kitchen, library, pool tables and hair salon. Park approval required before offer can be accepted, 2 pets OK, no rentals allowed. Great location in the park and in Bellingham.

Seize the opportunity to own this 3 Bed 2 bath home offered at an unmatched $455k! Boasting an open layout with a versatile extra living area downstairs that doubles as a 4th primary bedroom. Freshly painted interiors are complemented by vaulted ceilings, new appliances, tankless water heater and a brand new wrap-around deck, perfect for enjoying the surroundings. This property features a rare, sizable yard with a large shed for additional storage, a gem in the Sudden Valley community. Located conveniently inside Gate 3, this home offers full access to Sudden Valley's coveted amenities, including a golf course, lake access, clubhouse with swimming pool, and boat launches. Embrace a lifestyle of comfort and convenience in this inviting home.

A view to die for. New home located in the highly sought after Lake Samish Terrace Park. This quiet 55+ setting has private lake access with park, dock, and a friendly environment. Home has a primary bedroom and 2nd office or guest bedroom with lots of windows to bring in added lighting. Stainless steel appliances add to the cleanliness and quaintness of the setting. The covered front porch overlooks a private park, Lake Samish and the mountains. Longer driveway for several cars as needed. Backs to an open forest/orchard area for added privacy. Space rent includes water, sewer and basic cable making it very reasonable. Shed in the backyard allows for easy storage.

Rare 1.65 acre parcel. Bones of the house appear to be good, but home is a tear down or fixer upper. Value is in the land. Surrounded by farmland, the property has lots of large Cedar and Fir trees. There is a large shop with multiple other outbuildings.

Opportunity in Nooksack! A FIXER home in an established neighborhood. Very residential and is not a main street. To the north an established row of fir trees and adjacent large field. In the distance a great view of the Canadian Coastal Range mountains. From behind the home, a view of the foothills. This home has not flooded. Home has 1, 056 SF with an attached garage at 364 SF. Built in 1984. 3 BR, 1 BA. Large front deck that is west facing. Home is at the end of the street. Nicely fenced on the southside. Vacant field on the northside and behind the home. 10 x 10 shed also on the property. Lot is .24 acre. Rehab Loan would be a possibility. Due to estate sale items in yard & in home will not be removed. AS IS.

A remarkable forested retreat located by Lake Whatcom, above Agate Bay, off Northshore Rd. Astounding backyard with a back porch overlooking Carpenter Creek below and private wooded area. Lake Whatcom beach rights and dock space only minutes away. The combination of the back porch and the lake frontage community dock makes this a great opportunity! 2006 manu home in great condition & style, 2 BR & 2 full baths, 784 SF. Well built front porch. New roof 2023, Two solid outbuildings. Parking for 3 cars w/ ease. All ages park, no rentals with 25 homes only. Can be second home or year 'round. Space lease $800/month covers water/sewer, garbage. Sheetrock interior includes two skylights. Outdoor sauna not included unless with a good offer.

Dreaming of owning your own private mountain view estate? You've found it here in this sun drenched 3 bed/2.5 bath 1.68 acre home surrounded by open space, mature landscaping & fruit trees. The convenient main level living design features a luxurious primary suite along with the open concept kitchen/living/dining floor plan popular with the modern buyer. Delight in the custom details that make all the difference: soft close cabinetry, solid core doors, triple pane windows, extra sound proof insulation, etc. The covered west facing deck is the ideal place to relax or entertain while enjoying the stunning sunsets. Loads of space for parking + RV ready (water, power, dump). This is Pacific Northwest living at its' finest...don't miss it!
